The Chronicle THE Minister of Environment, Climate, Tourism and Hospitality Industry, Nqobizitha Mangaliso Ndlovu, is in Mutare where he is attending the Forest Industries Training Centre and Zimbabwe College of Forestry 2021 Graduation Ceremony. The graduation is being conducted under the theme ‘Promoting a Green Economy through Forestry Training’. The minister kicked off the proceedings with a tree planting ceremony this morning. Also present is the host Manicaland Minister of Provincial Affairs and Devolution, Cde Nokuthula Matsikenyeri, director of tourism in the ministry Dr Douglas Runyowa, Forestry Commission general manager, Abednico Marufu and ZTA acting chief executive, Givemore Chidzidzi among others. 